cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC 

This paper deals with online learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization and game theory concepts, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of probability bounds and regret analysis suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves the study of multi-armed bandit problems, which are a common topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
